        <section>
            <ul>
                <li class="row">
                    <div class="col-s-2">
                        <img src="/Css/images/temp/clock.png" class="hidden-xs" />
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-s-10">
                        <h4>Caught Off Guard</h4>
                        <p>Someone is trying to attack you by surprise. If - and only if - it is logically possible to spot the foe before being attacked, you may flip a coin by typing /roll passfail. On Pass, you may roll defense as normal. On Fail, you are Caught Off Guard for one round, and take a temporary -3 penalty to your defense roll. There may be times that you are Caught Off Guard without flipping a coin! This penalty is gone on the following round. There are also times when it is more logical to simply take the hit without rolling.</p>
                    </div>
                </li>
                <li class="row">
                    <div class="col-s-2">
                        <img src="/Css/images/temp/clock.png" class="hidden-xs" />
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-s-10">
                        <h4>Flanked</h4>
                        <p>You are being attacked by two or more opponents on different sides. For any opponents you are not facing, take -1 to defense rolls. This condition is also applicable to being attacked from behind by one person without being able to immediately turn, such as some cases of being Restrained.</p>
                    </div>
                </li>
                <li class="row">
                    <div class="col-s-2">
                        <img src="/Css/images/temp/clock.png" class="hidden-xs" />
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-s-10">
                        <h4>Knocked Down</h4>
                        <p>You have been knocked to the ground. Any defense rolls you do against someone above you will receive a -2 penalty. If someone or something is on top of you, such as in the case of being tackled to the ground, you are also Restrained. Anyone who came down to the ground with you is also considered to be Knocked Down, though they do not take a penalty against you if they are on top of you.</p>
                        <p>There are several ways to lose the Knocked Down status.</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>If you are not in situation where someone has an invested interest in keeping you on the ground, such as a fight, then you may simply stand back up whenever it seems logical.</li>
                            <li>If you are not Restrained, but are in a fight, you may sacrifice an attack to attempt to stand. /roll passfail - on a Pass, you are able to stand.</li>
                            <li>If you are Restrained, you may first lose Restrained before attempting to stand. If you lose Restrained (which requires a Pass on /roll passfail), you may attempt to roll to your feet by passing two more /roll passfails in a row, in that round (for a total of three passes, including the one you rolled to lose Restrained).</li>
                            <li>Alternatively, you can attempt to roll on top of the person pinning you. To do this, you must pass an additional /roll passfail (so two consecutive Passes in the same round, including the one you did to lose Restrained). Then your opponent must /roll passfail. On Fail, you are able to roll on top of him.</li>
                            <li>If you lose Restrained, but do not succeed in pinning the other person or rolling to your feet, you may attempt to stand the next round. When no longer Restrained, you no longer take -2 against anyone else who is down on the ground with you.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </li>
                <li class="row">
                    <div class="col-s-2">
                        <img src="/Css/images/temp/clock.png" class="hidden-xs" />
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-s-10">
                        <h4>Kneeling</h4>
                        <p>Unless willfully on your knees for a strategic purpose, you take -2 for defense against anyone standing.</p>
                    </div>
                </li>
                <li class="row">
                    <div class="col-s-2">
                        <img src="/Css/images/temp/clock.png" class="hidden-xs" />
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-s-10">
                        <h4>On Fire</h4>
                        <p>And not in a good way! You are literally on fire, and suffer a -3 defense penalty until being extinguished. You may not attack with weapons while on fire. If you remain on fire for three straight rounds, you become incapacitated and will die without immediate medical attention. Better stop, drop, and roll. Protection or resistances to fire may reduce or nullify these effects.</p>
                    </div>
                </li>
                <li class="row">
                    <div class="col-s-2">
                        <img src="/Css/images/temp/clock.png" class="hidden-xs" />
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-s-10">
                        <h4>Restrained</h4>
                        <p>You have become partially restrained, either because someone has grabbed you, ensnared you, cuffed you, or otherwise. You cannot use the restrained limb until you break out of it; if your torso, chest, or back is restrained, you simply cannot escape until you break out of it. You may attempt to free yourself at the cost of attacking one target that round. A pass on a /roll passfail will free you. While restrained, you suffer a -1 to defense, and cannot move away.</p>
                    </div>
                </li>
            </ul>
